      • getIDs

        public static int[] getIDs(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack key)
        Get an array of all ID's engraved on a smithed key. If the specified item is not a smithed key, or an issue arises in the gathering of ID's, an empty integer array will be returned.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to get the ID's from
        Returns:
        an array of all ID's on the key

      • mergeKeys

        public static org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack mergeKeys(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack key1,
                                                       org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack key2,
                                                       int amount)
        Combine two smithed keys together to create multiple smithed key with the combined Key ID values. Values will be sorted in incremental order, and any duplicate values will be removed. If either of the keys are not smithed keys, the returned value will be null.
        Parameters:
        key1 - the first smithed key to merge
        key2 - the second smithed key to merge
        amount - the amount of keys to create
        Returns:
        keys with merged Key ID values. null if neither are smithed keys

      • mergeKeys

        public static org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack mergeKeys(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack key1,
                                                       org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack key2)
        Combine two smithed keys together to create a singular smithed key with the combined Key ID values. Values will be sorted in incremental order, and any duplicate values will be removed. If either of the keys are not smithed keys, the returned value will be null.
        Parameters:
        key1 - the first smithed key to merge
        key2 - the second smithed key to merge
        Returns:
        a singular key with merged Key ID values. null if neither are smithed keys
